The paper deals with a stochastic process and its convergence properties, which are typical topics in the subfield of Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The use of Markov chains and performance measures suggests that the paper could also be classified under Information Theory (cs.IT) or Probability (cs.PR). The concept of self-stabilization is relevant to the subfield of Control Systems (cs.SY), while the analysis of the cover time relates to the subfield of Mathematical Analysis (cs.MA).
